quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  8,49,"And recall what time the hypocrites and these in whose hearts was a disease said: their religion hath be gulfed those. And whosoever relieth on Allah then verily Allah is Mighty, Wise"
  8,50,"And couldst thou behold when the angels take away the life of those who disbelive striking their faces and their backs: taste the torment of burning"
  8,51,"This, because of that which your hands have sent forth, and verily Allah is never unjust unto His creatures"
  8,52,"Like are they unto the wont of the house of Fir'awn and those before them. They disbelieved in the signs of Allah, wherefore Allah laid hold of them for their sins. Verily Allah is strong, Severe in retribution"
  8,53,"This, because Allah is not one to change His favour wherewith He hath favoured a people until they have changed that which is in themselves; and verily Allah is Hearing, Knowing"
  8,54,"Like are they Unto the wont of the house of Fir'awn and those before them. They belied the signs of their Lord; wherefore We destroyed them for their sins, and drowned the house of fir'awn; and all of them were wrong-doers"
  8,55,Verily the vilest of moving creatures with Allah are those who disbelieve-wherefore they shall not believe
  8,56,"They with whom thou covenantedest, then they break their covenant every time, and they fear not"
  8,57,"Wherefore if thou over-takest them in war, disperse thou through them those behind them, that haply they may be admonished"
  8,58,And shouldst thou fear treachery from any people cast back then unto them their covenant to be equal. Verily Allah approveth not the treacherous